Kakeibo has you put your expenditures in four buckets: needs (fixed
expenses), leisure or wants (what you desire but isn=E2=80=99t necessary, l=
ike
ordering in or purchasing trendy clothes), culture (buying books), and
extras (unanticipated expenses or one-offs, like birthday gifts).

Each day, jot down what you spend in your ledger. Do this with pen and
paper, in real-time. This gives you a chance to slow down to become
