0" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer" style=3D"color:#be8100" target=3D"_blank">re=
sults go beyond</a> simply sticking to a budget and saving.</p>

<blockquote style=3D"background-color:#fafafa;color:#666;font-style:italic;=
margin-left:0;padding:20px 30px">
<p style=3D"color:#333">The Japanese believe that tidiness in one=E2=80=99s=
 finances is as important as tidiness in one=E2=80=99s house =E2=80=94 and =
indeed for them, the act of thinking mindfully about where one=E2=80=99s mo=
ney goes is in itself a recipe for calm and well-being.</p>
</blockquote>

<p style=3D"color:#333">To get started, all you need is to know is how much=
 money you have available and typically spend, plus a savings goal, and are=
as you=E2=80=99d like to improve. You=E2=80=99ll also need a pen and paper =
because this is a handwritten, visual practice.</p>

<h4 style=3D"font-family:calluna,Georgia,serif;color:#111;font-size:22px;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;margin-top:30px">How to use kakeibo</h4>

<p style=3D"color:#333">At the beginning of the month, you=E2=80=99ll figur=
e out your budget by subtracting your fixed expenses (rent, food, transport=
ation, medical, phone) from your income. You=E2=80=99ll also set a savings =
goal. Currently, this might seem impossible, but even a small amount does t=
he trick.</p>

<p style=3D"color:#333">Kakeibo has you put your expenditures in four bucke=
ts: needs (fixed expenses), leisure or wants (what you desire but isn=E2=80=
=99t necessary, like ordering in or purchasing trendy clothes), culture (bu=
ying books), and extras (unanticipated expenses or one-offs, like birthday =
gifts).</p>

<p style=3D"color:#333">Each day, jot down what you spend in your ledger. D=
o this with pen and paper, in real-time. This gives you a chance to slow do=
wn to become conscious of your habits in the present and consider how it ma=
y affect your future.</p>

<p style=3D"color:#333">At the end of the month, you=E2=80=99ll do a review=
 of what you spent, by bucket. Not only will you see the big picture of whe=
ther you stuck to your budget and managed to save, but you=E2=80=99ll also =
notice your successes and your challenges.</p>

<p style=3D"color:#333">Cultivating awareness helps relieve your worry and =
fear around money. Ultimately that=E2=80=99s the point of kakeibo: bringing=
 balance and peace of mind into your day-to-day life. And that in its own r=
ight is, well, like money in the bank.</p>

